⚠️  SSE STREAMING — IMPORTANT NOTES FOR POSTMAN USERS:

Postman does not render SSE streams in real time. The response will only appear after the full stream completes (or times out). This is a Postman limitation, not a bug in DocuMind.

**To properly test SSE streaming, use one of these instead:**

1. curl (recommended):
   curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/query/stream \
     -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
     -H 'Accept: text/event-stream' \
     -d '{"question": "What are the payment terms?", "doc_ids": ["<doc_id>"]}' \
     --no-buffer

2. Browser console (JavaScript):
   const res = await fetch('http://localhost:8000/query/stream', {
     method: 'POST',
     headers: {'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
     body: JSON.stringify({question: 'What are the payment terms?'})
   });
   const reader = res.body.getReader();
   const decoder = new TextDecoder();
   while (true) {
     const {done, value} = await reader.read();
     if (done) break;
     const chunk = decoder.decode(value);
     // Each chunk: 'data: <token>\n\n'
     const token = chunk.replace(/^data: /, '').replace(/\n\n$/, '');
     if (token !== '[DONE]') console.log(token);
   }

**SSE format:**
  Each token:  data: <token>\n\n
  Stream end:  data: [DONE]\n\n
  On error:    event: error\ndata: {"error": "..."}\n\n

